of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do
so, subject to the following conditions:

1. CONTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT FOR DEPLOYMENTS

   If you deploy, operate, or provide access to a version of this Software
   (including modified versions) that generates revenue, provides services to
   users, or operates as a commercial or non-commercial service, you MUST
   contribute a minimum of 11% (eleven percent) of your gross revenue or equivalent
   value to the Tuneable CIC main project.

   This contribution requirement applies to:
   - Any deployment of the Software that serves users (whether free or paid)
   - Any commercial use of the Software
   - Any derivative works or forks that are publicly accessible
   - Any service built using this Software that generates revenue

   The 11% contribution may be fulfilled through:
   - Direct financial contributions to Tuneable CIC
   - Code contributions (pull requests) of equivalent value
   - Infrastructure or resource sharing of equivalent value
   - Other contributions agreed upon with Tuneable CIC

2. CONTRIBUTION REPORTING

   You must report your contributions to Tuneable CIC on an annual basis,
   or more frequently if your annual revenue exceeds Â£100,000. Reports should
   be sent to: t@tuneable.stream

   Reports must include:
   - Total gross revenue or equivalent value generated
   - Calculated 11% contribution amount
   - Method of contribution (financial, code, resources, etc.)
   - Date of contribution

3. EXEMPTIONS

   The following uses are EXEMPT from the contribution requirement:
   - Personal, non-commercial use (not serving other users)
   - Development and testing environments
   - Educational or research purposes (non-commercial)
   - Contributions to the main Tuneable project itself

4. DEFINITIONS

   "Gross Revenue" means all revenue generated from the deployment, including
   but not limited to:
   - User subscriptions or payments
   - Advertising revenue
   - Transaction fees
   - Donations received
   - Any other income directly or indirectly related to the deployment

   "Equivalent Value" means the fair market value of non-financial contributions,
   as determined by Tuneable CIC in good faith.

5. ENFORCEMENT

   Failure to comply with the contribution requirement constitutes a breach of
   this license. Tuneable CIC reserves the right to:
   - Revoke your license to use the Software
   - Require immediate payment of outstanding contributions
   - Pursue legal remedies as appropriate

6. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY

   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
   FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
   AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER
   LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,
   OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN
   THE SOFTWARE.

7. COMMUNITY INTEREST COMPANY STATUS

   Tuneable CIC is a registered Community Interest Company committed to using
   all contributions for community benefit. All contributions received under
   this license will be used in accordance with Tuneable CIC's community
   interest objectives.

8. CONTACT

   For questions about this license or to arrange contributions:
   Email: t@tuneable.stream
   Website: https://tuneable.stream

---

This license is designed to ensure that the Tuneable platform continues to
benefit the music community while allowing others to build upon and deploy
the Software. The 11% contribution requirement helps sustain the main project
and ensures continued development for the benefit of all users.

